<BaseLayout
  title="Publications"
  description="Full list of publications by Prabhu Vellaisamy — 11 peer-reviewed papers + 5 workshop papers on LLM inference, deep learning accelerators, unary computing, and neuromorphic systems."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>Publications</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">11 peer-reviewed conference &amp; journal papers · 5 workshop papers · 1 under review · 2 preprints</p>
  </header>

  <!-- ── Under Review ───────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Under Review</h2>

    <div class="publication">
      <p class="publication-title">
        <span class="badge badge-review">Under Review</span>&ensp;TaxBreak: Unmasking the Hidden Costs of LLM Inference Through Overhead Decomposition
      </p>
      <p class="publication-authors">
        <strong>P. Vellaisamy</strong>, S. Tripathi, V. Natarajan, S.S. Thenarasu, R.D.S. Blanton, J.P. Shen
      </p>
      <p class="publication-venue">
        <em>IEEE ISPASS 2026</em> [Submitted] · <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.12465" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">arXiv:2603.12465</a>
      </p>
      <p class="pub-note">Introduces TaxBreak, a trace-driven methodology decomposing host-visible orchestration overhead into framework translation time, CUDA library translation time, and kernel launch-path time. Derives the Host-Device Balance Index (HDBI). Validated on NVIDIA H100 and H200.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Preprints ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Preprints</h2>

    <div class="publication">
      <p class="publication-title">
        <span class="badge badge-review">Preprint</span>&ensp;NeuroAI Temporal Neural Networks (NeuTNNs): Microarchitecture and Design Framework for Specialized Neuromorphic Processing Units
      </p>
      <p class="publication-authors">
        S. Venkatachalam, <strong>P. Vellaisamy</strong>, H. Nair, W.C. Huang, Y. Na, Y. Kang, Q. Jacobson, J.P. Shen
      </p>
      <p class="publication-venue">
        Feb 2026 · <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.01546" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">arXiv:2602.01546</a>
      </p>
      <p class="pub-note">Introduces NeuTNNs with active dendrites and hierarchical proximal/distal segments, along with NeuTNNGen (PyTorch-to-layout tool suite). Synaptic pruning reduces synapse counts and hardware costs by 30–50% while maintaining precision across diverse sensory modalities.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="publication">
      <p class="publication-title">
        <span class="badge badge-review">Preprint</span>&ensp;A-Graph: A Unified Graph Representation for At-Will Simulation across System Stacks
      </p>
      <p class="publication-authors">
        D. Price, <strong>P. Vellaisamy</strong>, P. Gonzalez, G. Michelogiannakis, J.P. Shen, D. Wu
      </p>
      <p class="publication-venue">
        Feb 2026 · <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.04847" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">arXiv:2602.04847</a>
      </p>
      <p class="pub-note">Architecture-Graph (Agraph) unifies the system representation surrounding any arbitrary application, software stack, and architecture to enable automated cross-stack optimization and design space exploration.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

